HEADWORD: Philosophical
<hw>Phil`o*soph"ic*al</hw>
<pr>(?)</pr>, }</mhw> <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L. <ets>philosophicus</ets>:
cf. F. <ets>philosophique</ets>.]</ety> <def>Of or pertaining to
philosophy; versed in, or imbued with, the principles of philosophy;
hence, characterizing a philosopher; rational; wise; temperate; calm;
cool.</def> -- <wordforms><wf>Phil`o*soph"ic*al*ly</wf>,
<pos>adv.</pos></wordforms>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

